@Ferlord, that "odd" body ensures that opponents using Blue's nemesis color will have to zap it at least twice. (Well, four times [if we're being literal](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=23075)). They have to spend their own turn taking care of this bastard of a card instead of clearing *your* field on *your* turn.  

Anyway, what an incredible card. One of the biggest wrenches you can throw in any enemy's plans, especially in the blue mirror match. With Teferi, you save your mana to counter their spells like normal. But wait! Instead of untapping and going on your way like normal, [just](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=205029) [throw](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=189213) [your](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=154081) [creature](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=106426) [of](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=78697) [choice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=74445) on their turn so it's ready to beat face and/or activate its ability on yours.  

